obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31816)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 16th August, 1954, see Gazette of India 1954, Part II, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550&sectionId=31816&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Shillong (Rifle Range and`
  line `Umlong) Cantonments Assimilation of Laws Act, 1954.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31817)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550&sectionId=31817&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act:--`
  line
  line `(a) appointed day means the date appointed under sub-section (2) of section 1 for the coming`
  line `into force of this Act.`
  line
  line `(b) law means so much of any Act, Ordinance, Regulation, rule, order or bye-law as relates to`
  line `any of the matters enumerated in Lists I and III in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "scheduled areas means, the areas specified in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31818)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Assimilation of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550&sectionId=31818&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws which immediately before the appointed day extend to, or`
  line `are in force in the scheduled areas shall on that day cease to be in force in the scheduled areas except`
  line `as respects things done or omitted to be done before that day, and for the removal of doubts, it is`
  line `herby declared that section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply in relation to`
  line `such successor as it applies in relation to the repeal of an enactment by a Central Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All laws which immediately before the appointed day extend to, or in force in, the Khasi and`
  line `Jaintia Hills District shall as from that day extend to and be in force in the scheduled areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31819)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550&sectionId=31819&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_000010_195431_1517807322550
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in relation to the transition under section 3`
  line `from one law or group of laws to another law or group of laws, the Central Government may, by order`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette, make such provisions as it considers necessary for the removal of the`
  line difficulty.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
